Looks like there are cache misses possibly leading to larger latencies:   Exa:  OpStreamCacheHelper: Cache miss due to stored format mismatch. (Json, D) [https://portal.microsoftgeneva.com/s/27C058B5] GetSnapshotFromCache: cache miss - got empty value for key: 1dead407-e6dd-4ba4-8d05-fd1abbe5cda7_ddff7dd1-8db8-4b15-b6b1-fe22d0eaf91a [https://portal.microsoftgeneva.com/s/DFBD4E98]

For the consumer tenant, SPO passes a token to Push and Push is supposed to use that token when calling back into SPO. That token is refreshed in the Redis session data whenever clients call joinSession. However, Push caches the session info in-memory. So it's possible for a long running session to start seeing expiredToken errors if that in-memory token value was used for over 24hrs.
